      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LIKE CLOCKWORK (8) showed plenty of ability in her debut campaign, flying late over 1000m prior to the break. Her trial coming into this was very impressive and the booking of Pike is a big push for her chances. She looks a progressive type who can return with a bang. AWESOME BOY (4) finished off strongly over 1000m on resumption and looks better suited getting out to 1200m now. He'll need some luck from a wide draw, but his best form is good enough to see him end his winning drought. AHYEAHRIGHTO (1) trialled well coming in and finished off nicely to be 0.7L off the winner here a fortnight ago. Rates highly on the back of that effort and creates plenty of interest with that run under his belt. Improvement is likely and he can make a statement. GOD HAS DRIFTED (3) is in winning form and can't be discounted.",
